---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Sprint 1 scaffolds this surface; it becomes meaningful when content lands (ADR-0009 §6, Sprint 3+).
// There are no topic pages yet because there are no topics — content/ is empty, and generating
// placeholder topics would produce exactly the thin, worthless pages that SEO punishes.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="WhyStack — learn why technologies exist"
  description="An engineering learning platform that teaches why technologies exist, which problems they solve, and when not to use them. Version-aware, bilingual, offline-capable."
>
  <h1>WhyStack</h1>

  <p>
    Most documentation tells you <em>how</em>. WhyStack tells you <strong>why</strong> — why a
    technology exists, which problem it actually solves, what it costs you, and when not to reach for
    it.
  </p>

  <h2>This surface is not the product</h2>

  <p>
    These pages are the public, readable half. They are static HTML — no application bundle, no
    JavaScript, no login — so that a search engine, an AI crawler, or someone on a slow connection can
    read a topic without downloading an app first.
  </p>

  <p>
    Progress, quizzes, bookmarks, roadmaps and offline Knowledge Packs live in the application. This
    surface exists so the content can be <em>found</em>.
  </p>

  <h2>Nothing is published yet</h2>

  <p>
    Content is written, reviewed and published from the content repository, and the first topics land
    in Sprint 3. This page is the generator proving it works — it is not a placeholder for a topic
    that failed to build.
  </p>

  <p>
    The code is open: <a href="https://github.com/itolgayazgi/whystack">github.com/itolgayazgi/whystack</a>
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
